16. Write a Java program to get a date after 2 weeks.

import java.util.*;
public class Exercise16 {
   public static void main(String[] args)
    {
     //two weeks
     int noOfDays = 14; 
     Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();
     Date cdate = cal.getTime();
     cal.add(Calendar.DAY_OF_YEAR, noOfDays);
     Date date = cal.getTime();
     System.out.println("\nCurrent Date: " + cdate+"\n");  
     System.out.println("Day after two weeks: " + date+"\n");  	
    }
}


>>
Current Date: Tue Jun 20 17:12:49 IST 2017                                                                    
Day after two weeks: Tue Jul 04 17:12:49 IST 2017 
N.B.: The result may varry for your system date and time.
